Note:
AArch64 Instruction Encoder - Binary Machine Code Generation

Encodes AArch64 instructions into their fixed 32-bit binary representation for direct
object file emission (bypassing the assembler). All AArch64 instructions are exactly
4 bytes (32 bits), simplifying encoding compared to x86_64's variable-length encoding.

This file performs the following tasks:
- Encodes data-processing (register) instructions: ADD, SUB, AND, ORR, EOR, etc.
- Encodes data-processing (immediate) instructions: ADD imm, SUB imm, MOV imm
- Encodes load/store instructions with various addressing modes
- Encodes branch instructions: B, B.cond, BL, BR, BLR, RET
- Encodes system instructions: SVC, NOP, DMB, DSB, ISB
- Encodes floating-point data-processing instructions
- Maps LIR opcodes to binary encodings via encode_lir_instruction

AArch64 encoding format reference:
  All instructions are 32 bits with the following major format groups:

  Data Processing (Register):
    |sf(1)|opc(2)|S(1)|11010|shift(2)|0|Rm(5)|imm6(6)|Rn(5)|Rd(5)|
    sf=1 for 64-bit (X registers), sf=0 for 32-bit (W registers)

  Data Processing (Immediate):
    |sf(1)|opc(2)|S(1)|100010|sh(1)|imm12(12)|Rn(5)|Rd(5)|   (ADD/SUB imm)
    |opc(2)|10010|hw(2)|imm16(16)|Rd(5)|                      (MOVZ/MOVK/MOVN)

  Load/Store (Unsigned Immediate Offset):
    |size(2)|111001|opc(2)|imm12(12)|Rn(5)|Rt(5)|

  Load/Store (Pre/Post-Index):
    |size(2)|111000|opc(2)|0|imm9(9)|op(1)|1|Rn(5)|Rt(5)|

  Load/Store Pair:
    |opc(2)|10100|L(1)|imm7(7)|Rt2(5)|Rn(5)|Rt(5)|

  Branch (Unconditional):
    |op(1)|00101|imm26(26)|        B=0, BL=1

  Branch (Conditional):
    |01010100|imm19(19)|0|cond(4)|

  Branch (Register):
    |1101011|opc(4)|11111|000000|Rn(5)|00000|     BR/BLR/RET

  System:
    |11010101|L(1)|op0(2)|op1(3)|CRn(4)|CRm(4)|op2(3)|Rt(5)|

Dependencies:
- Imports calling_convention.runa for register ID constants
- Imports layout.runa for binary output buffer allocation
- Imports list.runa for instruction sequence building
:End Note

Import "compiler/backend/machine_code/aarch64/calling_convention.runa" as CallingConv
Import "compiler/backend/machine_code/common/machine_code_interface.runa" as MachineCode
Import "compiler/frontend/primitives/memory/layout.runa" as Layout
Import "compiler/frontend/primitives/collections/list.runa" as List

Note: ============================================================================
Note: Encoding Constants
Note: ============================================================================

@Reasoning
AArch64 condition codes for B.cond instructions. These are 4-bit values encoded
in bits [3:0] of conditional branch instructions.
@End Reasoning

Constant COND_EQ as Integer is 0    Note: Equal (Z=1)
Constant COND_NE as Integer is 1    Note: Not equal (Z=0)
Constant COND_HS as Integer is 2    Note: Unsigned higher or same (C=1), alias CS
Constant COND_LO as Integer is 3    Note: Unsigned lower (C=0), alias CC
Constant COND_MI as Integer is 4    Note: Minus/negative (N=1)
Constant COND_PL as Integer is 5    Note: Plus/positive or zero (N=0)
Constant COND_VS as Integer is 6    Note: Overflow (V=1)
Constant COND_VC as Integer is 7    Note: No overflow (V=0)
Constant COND_HI as Integer is 8    Note: Unsigned higher (C=1 and Z=0)
Constant COND_LS as Integer is 9    Note: Unsigned lower or same (C=0 or Z=1)
Constant COND_GE as Integer is 10   Note: Signed greater or equal (N=V)
Constant COND_LT as Integer is 11   Note: Signed less than (N!=V)
Constant COND_GT as Integer is 12   Note: Signed greater than (Z=0 and N=V)
Constant COND_LE as Integer is 13   Note: Signed less or equal (Z=1 or N!=V)
Constant COND_AL as Integer is 14   Note: Always (unconditional)
Constant COND_NV as Integer is 15   Note: Never (reserved, behaves as AL)

Note: sf bit values for operand size
Constant SF_32 as Integer is 0      Note: 32-bit operation (W registers)
Constant SF_64 as Integer is 1      Note: 64-bit operation (X registers)

Note: ============================================================================
Note: Register ID to Hardware Encoding
Note: ============================================================================

@Reasoning
AArch64 hardware register encoding is straightforward: X0-X30 are encoded as 0-30
in the 5-bit register fields. SP and XZR share encoding 31, distinguished by
instruction context (SP in load/store base, XZR in data processing).

Our internal register IDs 0-30 map directly to hardware encoding. FPR IDs 32-63
map to hardware encoding 0-31 (subtract 32). SP(31) maps to hardware 31. XZR(65)
maps to hardware 31.
@End Reasoning

Process called "encode_gpr" that takes reg_id as Integer returns Integer:
    Note: Maps internal register ID to 5-bit hardware encoding
    If reg_id is greater than or equal to 0:
        If reg_id is less than or equal to 30:
            Return reg_id
        End If
    End If
    Note: SP(31) and XZR(65) both encode as 31
    If reg_id is 31:
        Return 31
    End If
    If reg_id is 65:
        Return 31
    End If
    Return 0
End Process

Process called "encode_fpr" that takes reg_id as Integer returns Integer:
    Note: Maps internal FPR register ID (32-63) to 5-bit hardware encoding (0-31)
    If reg_id is greater than or equal to 32:
        If reg_id is less than or equal to 63:
            Return reg_id minus 32
        End If
    End If
    Return 0
End Process

Note: ============================================================================
Note: Data Processing (Register) Encoders
Note: ============================================================================

@Reasoning
ADD (shifted register) encoding:
  |sf|0|0|01011|shift|0|Rm|imm6|Rn|Rd|
  Bits [31]: sf (1=64-bit, 0=32-bit)
  Bits [30:29]: opc (00=ADD)
  Bits [28:24]: 01011
  Bits [23:22]: shift type (00=LSL, 01=LSR, 10=ASR)
  Bits [21]: 0
  Bits [20:16]: Rm (source register 2)
  Bits [15:10]: imm6 (shift amount, 0 for no shift)
  Bits [9:5]: Rn (source register 1)
  Bits [4:0]: Rd (destination register)

For ADD Xd, Xn, Xm with no shift:
  Binary: 1|00|01011|00|0|Rm|000000|Rn|Rd
  Hex base: 0x8B000000 (64-bit) or 0x0B000000 (32-bit)
@End Reasoning

Process called "encode_add_reg" that takes rd as Integer, rn as Integer, rm as Integer, sf as Integer returns Integer:
    Let rd_enc be encode_gpr(rd)
    Let rn_enc be encode_gpr(rn)
    Let rm_enc be encode_gpr(rm)

    Note: Base encoding for ADD (shifted register): sf|00|01011|shift=00|0|Rm|imm6=0|Rn|Rd
    Let encoding be 0

    Note: Set sf bit [31]
    If sf is SF_64:
        Set encoding to encoding plus 2147483648  Note: 1 shifted left by 31 = 0x80000000
    End If

    Note: Set opcode bits [28:24] = 01011 = 0x0B
    Set encoding to encoding plus 184549376       Note: 0x0B000000

    Note: Set Rm field [20:16]
    Set encoding to encoding plus (rm_enc multiplied by 65536)

    Note: Set Rn field [9:5]
    Set encoding to encoding plus (rn_enc multiplied by 32)

    Note: Set Rd field [4:0]
    Set encoding to encoding plus rd_enc

    Return encoding
End Process

@Reasoning
SUB (shifted register) encoding:
  |sf|1|0|01011|shift|0|Rm|imm6|Rn|Rd|
  Same as ADD but opc bits [30:29] = 10 instead of 00.
  Hex base: 0xCB000000 (64-bit) or 0x4B000000 (32-bit)
@End Reasoning

Process called "encode_sub_reg" that takes rd as Integer, rn as Integer, rm as Integer, sf as Integer returns Integer:
    Let rd_enc be encode_gpr(rd)
    Let rn_enc be encode_gpr(rn)
    Let rm_enc be encode_gpr(rm)

    Let encoding be 0

    Note: Set sf bit [31]
    If sf is SF_64:
        Set encoding to encoding plus 2147483648  Note: 0x80000000
    End If

    Note: Set opc=10 [30:29] and fixed bits [28:24] = 01011
    Note: opc bit [30] = 1 -> add 0x40000000
    Set encoding to encoding plus 1073741824      Note: 0x40000000
    Set encoding to encoding plus 184549376       Note: 0x0B000000

    Note: Set Rm field [20:16]
    Set encoding to encoding plus (rm_enc multiplied by 65536)

    Note: Set Rn field [9:5]
    Set encoding to encoding plus (rn_enc multiplied by 32)

    Note: Set Rd field [4:0]
    Set encoding to encoding plus rd_enc

    Return encoding
End Process

@Reasoning
MOV (register) is an alias for ORR Xd, XZR, Xm on AArch64.
ORR (shifted register) encoding:
  |sf|01|01010|shift|0|Rm|imm6|Rn|Rd|
  With Rn=XZR(31) and shift=0, imm6=0, this implements MOV Xd, Xm.
  Hex base: 0xAA000000 (64-bit) or 0x2A000000 (32-bit), Rn=XZR=31
@End Reasoning

Process called "encode_mov_reg" that takes rd as Integer, rm as Integer, sf as Integer returns Integer:
    Let rd_enc be encode_gpr(rd)
    Let rm_enc be encode_gpr(rm)
    Let xzr_enc be 31  Note: XZR hardware encoding

    Let encoding be 0

    Note: Set sf bit [31]
    If sf is SF_64:
        Set encoding to encoding plus 2147483648  Note: 0x80000000
    End If

    Note: ORR base: opc=01 [30:29], fixed [28:24]=01010
    Note: 0x2A000000 = 01|01010|00|0|00000|000000|00000|00000
    Set encoding to encoding plus 704643072       Note: 0x2A000000

    Note: Set Rm field [20:16]
    Set encoding to encoding plus (rm_enc multiplied by 65536)

    Note: Set Rn field [9:5] = XZR (31)
    Set encoding to encoding plus (xzr_enc multiplied by 32)

    Note: Set Rd field [4:0]
    Set encoding to encoding plus rd_enc

    Return encoding
End Process

Note: ============================================================================
Note: Load/Store (Unsigned Immediate Offset) Encoders
Note: ============================================================================

@Reasoning
LDR (unsigned immediate offset) encoding:
  |size|111001|opc|imm12|Rn|Rt|
  Bits [31:30]: size (11=64-bit/X, 10=32-bit/W)
  Bits [29:24]: 111001
  Bits [23:22]: opc (01=LDR, 00=STR)
  Bits [21:10]: imm12 (unsigned offset, scaled by size: 8 for 64-bit, 4 for 32-bit)
  Bits [9:5]: Rn (base register)
  Bits [4:0]: Rt (transfer register)

For LDR Xt, [Xn, #offset]:
  size=11, opc=01
  imm12 = offset / 8 (offset must be multiple of 8 for 64-bit)
  Base: 0xF9400000 (64-bit LDR)
@End Reasoning

Process called "encode_ldr_imm" that takes rt as Integer, rn as Integer, offset as Integer, size_bits as Integer returns Integer:
    Let rt_enc be encode_gpr(rt)
    Let rn_enc be encode_gpr(rn)

    Let encoding be 0

    Note: Size field [31:30] and opc field [23:22]
    Note: size_bits: 3=64-bit(X), 2=32-bit(W), 1=16-bit(H), 0=8-bit(B)
    If size_bits is 3:
        Note: 64-bit LDR: size=11, opc=01 -> 0xF9400000
        Set encoding to 4182573056  Note: 0xF9400000
        Note: Scale offset by 8
        Let scaled_offset be offset divided by 8
        Note: imm12 field [21:10]
        Set encoding to encoding plus (scaled_offset multiplied by 1024)
    End If
    If size_bits is 2:
        Note: 32-bit LDR: size=10, opc=01 -> 0xB9400000
        Set encoding to 3108438016  Note: 0xB9400000
        Set scaled_offset to offset divided by 4
        Set encoding to encoding plus (scaled_offset multiplied by 1024)
    End If
    If size_bits is 1:
        Note: 16-bit LDRH: size=01, opc=01 -> 0x79400000
        Set encoding to 2034302976  Note: 0x79400000
        Set scaled_offset to offset divided by 2
        Set encoding to encoding plus (scaled_offset multiplied by 1024)
    End If
    If size_bits is 0:
        Note: 8-bit LDRB: size=00, opc=01 -> 0x39400000
        Set encoding to 960167936   Note: 0x39400000
        Set encoding to encoding plus (offset multiplied by 1024)
    End If

    Note: Set Rn field [9:5]
    Set encoding to encoding plus (rn_enc multiplied by 32)

    Note: Set Rt field [4:0]
    Set encoding to encoding plus rt_enc

    Return encoding
End Process

@Reasoning
STR (unsigned immediate offset) encoding:
  Same format as LDR but with opc=00 instead of opc=01.
  Base: 0xF9000000 (64-bit STR)
@End Reasoning

Process called "encode_str_imm" that takes rt as Integer, rn as Integer, offset as Integer, size_bits as Integer returns Integer:
    Let rt_enc be encode_gpr(rt)
    Let rn_enc be encode_gpr(rn)

    Let encoding be 0

    If size_bits is 3:
        Note: 64-bit STR: size=11, opc=00 -> 0xF9000000
        Set encoding to 4177326080  Note: 0xF9000000
        Let scaled_offset be offset divided by 8
        Set encoding to encoding plus (scaled_offset multiplied by 1024)
    End If
    If size_bits is 2:
        Note: 32-bit STR: size=10, opc=00 -> 0xB9000000
        Set encoding to 3103191040  Note: 0xB9000000
        Set scaled_offset to offset divided by 4
        Set encoding to encoding plus (scaled_offset multiplied by 1024)
    End If
    If size_bits is 1:
        Note: 16-bit STRH: size=01, opc=00 -> 0x79000000
        Set encoding to 2029056000  Note: 0x79000000
        Set scaled_offset to offset divided by 2
        Set encoding to encoding plus (scaled_offset multiplied by 1024)
    End If
    If size_bits is 0:
        Note: 8-bit STRB: size=00, opc=00 -> 0x39000000
        Set encoding to 954920960   Note: 0x39000000
        Set encoding to encoding plus (offset multiplied by 1024)
    End If

    Note: Set Rn field [9:5]
    Set encoding to encoding plus (rn_enc multiplied by 32)

    Note: Set Rt field [4:0]
    Set encoding to encoding plus rt_enc

    Return encoding
End Process

Note: ============================================================================
Note: Branch Encoders
Note: ============================================================================

@Reasoning
B (unconditional branch) encoding:
  |0|00101|imm26|
  Bits [31]: op=0 (B, not BL)
  Bits [30:26]: 00101
  Bits [25:0]: imm26 (signed offset in instructions, PC-relative: target = PC + imm26*4)

  The imm26 field allows a +/-128 MB range.
  Base: 0x14000000
@End Reasoning

Process called "encode_b" that takes offset_instructions as Integer returns Integer:
    Note: B encoding: op=0, opc=00101, imm26
    Note: offset_instructions is signed offset in number of instructions (4 bytes each)
    Let encoding be 335544320  Note: 0x14000000

    Note: Mask imm26 to 26 bits (handle negative offsets via two's complement)
    Let imm26 be offset_instructions
    Note: Mask to 26 bits: imm26 bitwise and 0x03FFFFFF
    If imm26 is less than 0:
        Note: Convert negative to two's complement 26-bit
        Set imm26 to imm26 plus 67108864  Note: 2^26 = 0x4000000
    End If
    Let masked be imm26 modulo by 67108864  Note: bitwise and 0x03FFFFFF

    Set encoding to encoding plus masked

    Return encoding
End Process

@Reasoning
B.cond (conditional branch) encoding:
  |01010100|imm19|0|cond|
  Bits [31:24]: 01010100 = 0x54
  Bits [23:5]: imm19 (signed offset in instructions, PC-relative)
  Bits [4]: 0
  Bits [3:0]: cond (condition code, 4 bits)

  Base: 0x54000000
  The imm19 field allows a +/-1 MB range.
@End Reasoning

Process called "encode_b_cond" that takes offset_instructions as Integer, cond as Integer returns Integer:
    Let encoding be 1409286144  Note: 0x54000000

    Note: Mask imm19 to 19 bits
    Let imm19 be offset_instructions
    If imm19 is less than 0:
        Set imm19 to imm19 plus 524288  Note: 2^19
    End If
    Let masked_imm be imm19 modulo by 524288  Note: bitwise and 0x7FFFF

    Note: imm19 goes in bits [23:5]
    Set encoding to encoding plus (masked_imm multiplied by 32)

    Note: Condition code in bits [3:0]
    Set encoding to encoding plus cond

    Return encoding
End Process

@Reasoning
BL (branch with link) encoding:
  |1|00101|imm26|
  Same as B but op=1 (bit [31] = 1), which saves return address in X30/LR.
  Base: 0x94000000
@End Reasoning

Process called "encode_bl" that takes offset_instructions as Integer returns Integer:
    Let encoding be 2483027968  Note: 0x94000000

    Let imm26 be offset_instructions
    If imm26 is less than 0:
        Set imm26 to imm26 plus 67108864
    End If
    Let masked be imm26 modulo by 67108864

    Set encoding to encoding plus masked

    Return encoding
End Process

@Reasoning
RET encoding:
  |1101011|0010|11111|000000|Rn|00000|
  Branch to address in Rn (default X30/LR).
  Bits [31:25]: 1101011
  Bits [24:21]: 0010 (opc for RET)
  Bits [20:16]: 11111
  Bits [15:10]: 000000
  Bits [9:5]: Rn (register containing return address, default X30=30)
  Bits [4:0]: 00000

  Base: 0xD65F0000
  For RET (using X30): 0xD65F03C0
@End Reasoning

Process called "encode_ret" that takes rn as Integer returns Integer:
    Let rn_enc be encode_gpr(rn)
    Note: RET base: 0xD65F0000
    Let encoding be 3596550144  Note: 0xD65F0000

    Note: Rn field [9:5]
    Set encoding to encoding plus (rn_enc multiplied by 32)

    Return encoding
End Process

@Reasoning
SVC (supervisor call) encoding:
  |11010100|000|imm16|000|01|
  Bits [31:24]: 11010100 = 0xD4
  Bits [23:21]: 000
  Bits [20:5]: imm16 (immediate value, typically 0 on Linux)
  Bits [4:2]: 000
  Bits [1:0]: 01 (SVC)

  Base: 0xD4000001
  SVC #0: 0xD4000001
@End Reasoning

Process called "encode_svc" that takes imm16 as Integer returns Integer:
    Note: SVC base: 0xD4000001
    Let encoding be 3556769793  Note: 0xD4000001

    Note: imm16 field [20:5]
    Set encoding to encoding plus (imm16 multiplied by 32)

    Return encoding
End Process

Note: ============================================================================
Note: LIR Instruction to Binary Encoding
Note: ============================================================================

@Reasoning
Maps a LIR instruction to its binary AArch64 encoding. This is the main dispatch
function for the binary encoder, used when emitting object files directly without
going through a text assembler.

The function reads the LIR instruction's opcode and operands, extracts register IDs
and immediate values, and calls the appropriate encoder function.

Parameters:
- instruction: pointer to an LIRInstruction
- output_buffer: pointer to binary output buffer
- buffer_offset: current write position in the buffer

Returns the number of bytes written (always 4 on AArch64, or 0 on error).
@End Reasoning

Process called "encode_lir_instruction" that takes instruction as Integer, output_buffer as Integer, buffer_offset as Integer returns Integer:
    If instruction is 0:
        Return 0
    End If
    If output_buffer is 0:
        Return 0
    End If

    Let opcode be __load(instruction, 0)
    Let result_ptr be __load(instruction, 8)
    Let op1_ptr be __load(instruction, 16)
    Let op2_ptr be __load(instruction, 24)

    Note: Extract register IDs from operands (0 = register type)
    Let rd be 0
    Let rn be 0
    Let rm be 0
    Let sf be SF_64

    If result_ptr is not 0:
        Let res_type be __load(result_ptr, 0)
        If res_type is 1:
            Set rd to __load(result_ptr, 8)
            Let res_size be __load(result_ptr, 56)
            If res_size is 4:
                Set sf to SF_32
            End If
        End If
    End If

    If op1_ptr is not 0:
        Let op1_type be __load(op1_ptr, 0)
        If op1_type is 1:
            Set rn to __load(op1_ptr, 8)
        End If
    End If

    If op2_ptr is not 0:
        Let op2_type be __load(op2_ptr, 0)
        If op2_type is 1:
            Set rm to __load(op2_ptr, 8)
        End If
    End If

    Let encoded be 0

    Note: NOP
    If opcode is 30000:
        Set encoded to 3573751839  Note: 0xD503201F (NOP encoding)
    End If

    Note: MOV
    If opcode is 30001:
        Set encoded to encode_mov_reg(rd, rn, sf)
    End If

    Note: ADD
    If opcode is 30100:
        Set encoded to encode_add_reg(rd, rn, rm, sf)
    End If

    Note: SUB
    If opcode is 30101:
        Set encoded to encode_sub_reg(rd, rn, rm, sf)
    End If

    Note: IMUL/MUL -> MADD Xd, Xn, Xm, XZR (multiply-add with zero addend)
    Note: MADD encoding: |sf|00|11011|000|Rm|0|Ra|Rn|Rd|
    Note: With Ra=XZR(31): Xd = Xn * Xm + 0 = Xn * Xm
    Note: Base: 0x9B007C00 (64-bit) or 0x1B007C00 (32-bit) with Ra=XZR bits [14:10]=11111
    If opcode is 30102:
        Let rd_enc be encode_gpr(rd)
        Let rn_enc be encode_gpr(rn)
        Let rm_enc be encode_gpr(rm)
        Set encoded to 0
        If sf is SF_64:
            Set encoded to encoded plus 2147483648  Note: sf=1
        End If
        Set encoded to encoded plus 452984832      Note: 0x1B000000 (base for MADD)
        Set encoded to encoded plus (rm_enc multiplied by 65536)
        Set encoded to encoded plus 31744           Note: Ra=XZR(31) in bits [14:10] = 31*32 = 992...
        Note: Actually Ra field is [14:10]: 31 * 1024 = 31744
        Set encoded to encoded plus (rn_enc multiplied by 32)
        Set encoded to encoded plus rd_enc
    End If

    If opcode is 30104:
        Note: Unsigned MUL same encoding as MADD with XZR
        Set rd_enc to encode_gpr(rd)
        Set rn_enc to encode_gpr(rn)
        Set rm_enc to encode_gpr(rm)
        Set encoded to 0
        If sf is SF_64:
            Set encoded to encoded plus 2147483648
        End If
        Set encoded to encoded plus 452984832
        Set encoded to encoded plus (rm_enc multiplied by 65536)
        Set encoded to encoded plus 31744
        Set encoded to encoded plus (rn_enc multiplied by 32)
        Set encoded to encoded plus rd_enc
    End If

    Note: SDIV: |sf|00|11010110|Rm|00001|1|Rn|Rd|
    Note: Base: 0x1AC00C00 (32-bit) or 0x9AC00C00 (64-bit)
    If opcode is 30103:
        Set rd_enc to encode_gpr(rd)
        Set rn_enc to encode_gpr(rn)
        Set rm_enc to encode_gpr(rm)
        Set encoded to 0
        If sf is SF_64:
            Set encoded to encoded plus 2147483648
        End If
        Set encoded to encoded plus 448790528      Note: 0x1AC00000
        Set encoded to encoded plus (rm_enc multiplied by 65536)
        Set encoded to encoded plus 3072            Note: 0x0C00 = opcode2 for SDIV
        Set encoded to encoded plus (rn_enc multiplied by 32)
        Set encoded to encoded plus rd_enc
    End If

    Note: UDIV: same as SDIV but opcode2=0x0800
    If opcode is 30105:
        Set rd_enc to encode_gpr(rd)
        Set rn_enc to encode_gpr(rn)
        Set rm_enc to encode_gpr(rm)
        Set encoded to 0
        If sf is SF_64:
            Set encoded to encoded plus 2147483648
        End If
        Set encoded to encoded plus 448790528
        Set encoded to encoded plus (rm_enc multiplied by 65536)
        Set encoded to encoded plus 2048            Note: 0x0800 = opcode2 for UDIV
        Set encoded to encoded plus (rn_enc multiplied by 32)
        Set encoded to encoded plus rd_enc
    End If

    Note: RET
    If opcode is 30522:
        Set encoded to encode_ret(30)  Note: RET with X30 (LR)
    End If

    Note: SVC (syscall)
    If opcode is 30523:
        Set encoded to encode_svc(0)
    End If

    Note: B (unconditional branch) - offset from operand
    If opcode is 30500:
        Let branch_offset be 0
        If op1_ptr is not 0:
            Set branch_offset to __load(op1_ptr, 16)
        End If
        Set encoded to encode_b(branch_offset)
    End If

    Note: Conditional branches (30501-30518)
    If opcode is 30501:
        Set branch_offset to 0
        If op1_ptr is not 0:
            Set branch_offset to __load(op1_ptr, 16)
        End If
        Set encoded to encode_b_cond(branch_offset, COND_EQ)
    End If
    If opcode is 30502:
        Set branch_offset to 0
        If op1_ptr is not 0:
            Set branch_offset to __load(op1_ptr, 16)
        End If
        Set encoded to encode_b_cond(branch_offset, COND_NE)
    End If
    If opcode is 30503:
        Set branch_offset to 0
        If op1_ptr is not 0:
            Set branch_offset to __load(op1_ptr, 16)
        End If
        Set encoded to encode_b_cond(branch_offset, COND_EQ)
    End If
    If opcode is 30504:
        Set branch_offset to 0
        If op1_ptr is not 0:
            Set branch_offset to __load(op1_ptr, 16)
        End If
        Set encoded to encode_b_cond(branch_offset, COND_NE)
    End If
    If opcode is 30505:
        Set branch_offset to 0
        If op1_ptr is not 0:
            Set branch_offset to __load(op1_ptr, 16)
        End If
        Set encoded to encode_b_cond(branch_offset, COND_LT)
    End If
    If opcode is 30506:
        Set branch_offset to 0
        If op1_ptr is not 0:
            Set branch_offset to __load(op1_ptr, 16)
        End If
        Set encoded to encode_b_cond(branch_offset, COND_LE)
    End If
    If opcode is 30507:
        Set branch_offset to 0
        If op1_ptr is not 0:
            Set branch_offset to __load(op1_ptr, 16)
        End If
        Set encoded to encode_b_cond(branch_offset, COND_GT)
    End If
    If opcode is 30508:
        Set branch_offset to 0
        If op1_ptr is not 0:
            Set branch_offset to __load(op1_ptr, 16)
        End If
        Set encoded to encode_b_cond(branch_offset, COND_GE)
    End If
    If opcode is 30509:
        Set branch_offset to 0
        If op1_ptr is not 0:
            Set branch_offset to __load(op1_ptr, 16)
        End If
        Set encoded to encode_b_cond(branch_offset, COND_LO)
    End If
    If opcode is 30510:
        Set branch_offset to 0
        If op1_ptr is not 0:
            Set branch_offset to __load(op1_ptr, 16)
        End If
        Set encoded to encode_b_cond(branch_offset, COND_LS)
    End If
    If opcode is 30511:
        Set branch_offset to 0
        If op1_ptr is not 0:
            Set branch_offset to __load(op1_ptr, 16)
        End If
        Set encoded to encode_b_cond(branch_offset, COND_HI)
    End If
    If opcode is 30512:
        Set branch_offset to 0
        If op1_ptr is not 0:
            Set branch_offset to __load(op1_ptr, 16)
        End If
        Set encoded to encode_b_cond(branch_offset, COND_HS)
    End If

    Note: BL (call)
    If opcode is 30520:
        Set branch_offset to 0
        If op1_ptr is not 0:
            Set branch_offset to __load(op1_ptr, 16)
        End If
        Set encoded to encode_bl(branch_offset)
    End If

    Note: LOAD (64-bit)
    If opcode is 30600:
        Let offset be 0
        If op1_ptr is not 0:
            Set op1_type to __load(op1_ptr, 0)
            If op1_type is 3:
                Set offset to __load(op1_ptr, 48)
                Set rn to __load(op1_ptr, 24)
            End If
        End If
        Set encoded to encode_ldr_imm(rd, rn, offset, 3)
    End If

    Note: STORE (64-bit)
    If opcode is 30601:
        Set offset to 0
        If op1_ptr is not 0:
            Set op1_type to __load(op1_ptr, 0)
            If op1_type is 3:
                Set offset to __load(op1_ptr, 48)
                Set rn to __load(op1_ptr, 24)
            End If
        End If
        Set encoded to encode_str_imm(rd, rn, offset, 3)
    End If

    Note: Write the 4-byte encoding to the output buffer (little-endian)
    __store8(output_buffer, buffer_offset, encoded modulo by 256)
    __store8(output_buffer, buffer_offset plus 1, (encoded divided by 256) modulo by 256)
    __store8(output_buffer, buffer_offset plus 2, (encoded divided by 65536) modulo by 256)
    __store8(output_buffer, buffer_offset plus 3, (encoded divided by 16777216) modulo by 256)

    Return 4
End Process
